abstract: >
  This repository contains the implementation of a multi-task reservoir
  computing system using VO₂ (vanadium dioxide) thermal neuristors as
  the physical computing substrate. A 28×28 array of thermally coupled
  VO₂ neuristors simultaneously solves three independent classification
  tasks — digit recognition, color classification, and parity detection —
  on a custom Colored MNIST dataset. Because the reservoir dynamics are
  fixed and only linear readout layers are trained, the system is immune
  to catastrophic forgetting by construction.

